The paper discusses a regularization technique for improving the performance of classifiers, particularly deep neural networks and support vector machines, in terms of both accuracy and robustness to adversarial attacks. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given the focus on deep neural networks and support vector machines, as well as the use of empirical and theoretical analysis to evaluate the proposed regularization technique, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
